<Layout 
title="Fishing Guides in Salem, Oregon"
description="Salem sits between the Willamette River and the North Santiam, with Detroit Lake and coastal rivers a day-trip away. Here’s a neutral directory of guides who regularly work these waters. Always confirm seasons, meeting ramps, and what’s included before you book."
url="https://salem.oregonfishingforum.com/guides/"
type="article"
site_name="Portland Fishing"
ogimage={srcImage.src}
footer_location="home"
>
    <div class="text-center">
        <MyH1 text="Fishing Guides in Salem, Oregon" />
        <p>
            Salem sits between the Willamette River and the North Santiam, with Detroit Lake and coastal rivers a day-trip away. Here’s a neutral directory of guides who regularly work these waters. Always confirm seasons, meeting ramps, and what’s included before you book.
        </p>
    </div>

<div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 mb-12">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="font-semibold">Dialed-in timing</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Local pros track Willamette springers, Santiam steelhead, and flow windows so you fish peak conditions.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="font-semibold">All the gear</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Rods, reels, tackle, safety gear—often included so you can just show up with a license and layers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="font-semibold">Access & safety</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Know the put-ins, take-outs, and safe flows on the Santiam and Willamette backchannels.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="font-semibold">Learn faster</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Casting, presentations, knots, and reading water—coaching turns into more hook-ups later.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

